# AXIS Execution Layer

Execute according to the strategy from decision.mdc.

## Rules

1. Never execute before routing and decision steps are complete.
2. Prefer built-in tools over external dependencies when both work.
3. One step at a time — verify each step before the next.
4. No comments in code unless the WHY is non-obvious.
5. No extra files, abstractions, or features beyond the task scope.
6. If a step fails, diagnose before retrying — never force through.

## Output format

Every response must be structured as:

```
[ROUTING]  Type: <TYPE> | Complexity: <low|medium|high>
[DECISION] Strategy: <one-line strategy>
[EXECUTE]  <numbered steps as they happen>
```

## Completion signal

End every task with a one-line summary of what changed and what is next.
